revisions.description: The private MIB file includes the DHCP Snooping profile.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2Enabled.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2Enabled
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2Enabled.description: If the value of this object is set to 'true', DHCP snooping is enabled.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindDbName.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindDbName
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindDbName.description: Name of the file that used to store binding information. If the value of the object is set to a zero-length string, the configuration will be removed.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRefreshIntvl.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRefreshIntvl
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRefreshIntvl.description: The refresh interval of the binding information in seconds.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRefresh.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRefresh
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRefresh.description: If the value of this object is set to 'on', the binding information will be refreshed immediately.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktSentNum.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktSentNum
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktSentNum.description: The total number of the packets send by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktRcvNum.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktRcvNum
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktRcvNum.description: The total number of the packets received by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktDropNum.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktDropNum
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2PktDropNum.description: The total number of the packets dropped by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindTable.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindTable
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindTable.description: The table containing information of DHCP clients listened by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindEntry
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindEntry.description: An entry containing information of DHCP clients.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindIpAddr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindIpAddr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindIpAddr.description: DHCP client's IP addresses collected by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindVlanId.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindVlanId
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindVlanId.description: DHCP client's VLAN ID collected by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindSecVlanId.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindSecVlanId
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindSecVlanId.description: DHCP client's second VLAN ID collected by DHCP snooping. 65535 means no second VLAN.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindMacAddr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindMacAddr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindMacAddr.description: DHCP client's MAC address collected by DHCP snooping.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindLease.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindLease
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindLease.description: Left lease time in seconds collected by DHCP snooping. The value of this object cannot be 0.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindPortIndex.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindPortIndex
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindPortIndex.description: DHCP client's port index collected by DHCP snooping. The value of zero means unknown port.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2BindRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfConfigTable.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfConfigTable
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfConfigTable.description: A table is used to configure DHCP snooping functions on ports.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfConfigEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfConfigEntry
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfConfigEntry.description: An entry containing DHCP snooping configurations of ports.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfCheckMac.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfCheckMac
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfCheckMac.description: If the value is 'true', MAC address of DHCP packets received on the port will be checked.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfCheckRequest.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfCheckRequest
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfCheckRequest.description: If the value is 'true', DHCP request packets will be checked.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfRateLimit.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfRateLimit
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfRateLimit.description: The rate limit in Kbps. If the value is 0, there is no rate limit on the port.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfRecordBind.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfRecordBind
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfRecordBind.description: If the value is 'true', information of DHCP packets received on the port will be recorded.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfMaxLearnNum.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfMaxLearnNum
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfMaxLearnNum.description: The maximum number of binding entries that could be learned on the port. If the value is 0, it means that there is no threshold on the port.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82Enable.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82Enable
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82Enable.description: If DHCP snooping supports option 82 functions, the value is 'true'. If DHCP snooping does NOT support option 82 functions, the value is 'false'.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82Strategy.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82Strategy
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82Strategy.description: The strategy of DHCP snooping handling option 82. 'drop' indicates DHCP snooping discarding the request packet including option 82. 'keep' indicates DHCP snooping accepting the request packet without any change of the option 82. 'replace' indicates DHCP snooping accepting the request packet on condition that it generates a new option 82 to replace the original one.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode.description: The mode of filling in the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'verbose' is the detailed mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDStr must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeType
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.description: Type of access node identifier that is used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 when the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOption82CIDMode is set to 'verbose'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode. 'invalid' indicates that the node identifier is NOT used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', the value of this object is set to 'invalid' automatically. Otherwise the value of this object cannot be set to 'invalid'. 'mac' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the bridge MAC of DHCP snooping device. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'mac'. 'sysname' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the sysname of the DHCP snooping. 'userDefine' indicates the node identifier is filled in with the string defined by the object of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr. If the value is set to 'userDefine', the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr must also be set to a non-zero length string.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the node identifier in the verbose mode. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', or the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeType is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set to a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode and hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDStr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDStr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 in the user-define mode. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set to a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDFormat.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDFormat
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDFormat.description: The format of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. 'undefine' is the undefine format. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'normal', this object is set with 'hex' automatically and cannot be set with 'undefine'. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'undefine'. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'userDefine', this object is set with 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set with other value. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82CIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode.description: The mode of filling in the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. 'sysname' is the sysname mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDStr must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDStr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDStr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the remote ID in the user-defined mode. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', this object is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDFormat.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDFormat
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDFormat.description: The format of DHCP option 82 remote ID in 'normal' mode. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'sysname' or 'userDefine', this object is set with 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set with other value. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'normal', the default value of this object is 'hex'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfOpt82RIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDTable.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDTable
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDTable.description: A table containing the information of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82 in VLAN.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDEntry
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDEntry.description: An entry containing the information of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82 in VLAN.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDStr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDStr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanCIDRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDTable.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDTable
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDTable.description: A table containing the information of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82 in VLAN.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDEntry.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDEntry
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDEntry.description: An entry containing the information of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82 in VLAN.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDMode.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDMode
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDMode.description: The mode of filling in the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82 in VLAN. 'sysname' indicates using the device sysname to fill in the suboption. 'userDefine' indicates using the string defined by hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDStr to fill in the suboption. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDStr must also be set.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDStr.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDStr
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDStr.description: The string used to fill in the remote ID suboption. If the value of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', this object is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDMode.

hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDRowStatus.name: hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDRowStatus
hpnicfDhcpSnoop2IfVlanRIDRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.
